12:14.965 --> 12:16.700
(francine singing,
bird chirping)

12:17.835 --> 12:19.169
Don't!

12:28.379 --> 12:31.948
¶ ¶

12:42.159 --> 12:43.993
(hissing)

12:45.663 --> 12:47.764
(yelling)

12:50.501 --> 12:52.902
(yelling, groaning)

12:52.970 --> 12:54.137
(both coughing)

12:54.205 --> 12:55.572
(yelling)

12:55.639 --> 12:59.142
Your chin is right
on my hipbone, kevin.

13:02.113 --> 13:04.748
Please, give me some rice.

13:04.815 --> 13:06.282
I'll do anything.

13:06.350 --> 13:09.319
I'll make you feel good.

13:10.521 --> 13:12.255
Steve, you did it!

13:12.323 --> 13:13.556
You saved me.

13:13.624 --> 13:14.491
I'm so proud of you!

13:19.397 --> 13:22.565
(mimics whirring
helicopter blades)

13:22.633 --> 13:25.602
(melancholic tune plays)

13:33.210 --> 13:34.778
(cell phone ringing)

13:34.845 --> 13:36.679
(whispering):
I'll call you back.

13:38.582 --> 13:39.816
You should have seen him.

13:39.884 --> 13:41.751
My boy, the war hero.

13:41.819 --> 13:43.520
Steve's gonna sing
the crap out of that

13:43.587 --> 13:45.155
National anthem now,
aren't you, steve?

13:47.124 --> 13:49.993
Did you have fun at the
reenactment, honey?

13:50.060 --> 13:53.463
That's right, real war heroes
don't need to talk about it.

13:53.531 --> 13:55.532
The same way I don't
talk about all the "tang"

13:55.599 --> 13:58.568
I got in college,
out of respect for my wife.

13:58.636 --> 14:00.336
Tons.

14:02.807 --> 14:04.507
Now, folks, we have
a very special

14:04.575 --> 14:06.409
Young man here tonight
who has the voice an angel.

14:06.477 --> 14:09.312
Let's hope
it's not the hell's angels!

14:09.380 --> 14:10.613
(laughter, cymbal clashes)

14:10.681 --> 14:11.981
Please welcome,

14:12.049 --> 14:14.684
To sing our national anthem,
steve smith!

14:14.752 --> 14:17.520
(applause)

14:19.123 --> 14:20.423
(clears throat)

14:20.491 --> 14:21.991
¶ oh, say... ¶

14:22.059 --> 14:23.793
(fireworks popping)

14:23.861 --> 14:25.094
<i>Fuh-fuh, fuh-fuh,
fuh-fuh, fuh-fuh.</i>

14:25.162 --> 14:26.563
<i>Fuh-fuh, fuh-fuh, fuh-fuh,
fuh-uh.</i>

14:28.098 --> 14:29.466
<i>No, you didn't!
Yes, I did!</i>

14:29.533 --> 14:30.733
<i>You're totally,
dead, bob.</i>

14:30.801 --> 14:33.036
<i>It's just us.
Just let me keep playing.</i>

14:33.103 --> 14:34.871
(rockets whistling)
vietcong! Vietcong!

14:34.939 --> 14:36.339
(screaming)

14:38.075 --> 14:39.175
Cong!

14:39.243 --> 14:40.276
(imitates rapid gunfire)

14:40.344 --> 14:41.311
(imitates
gunfire)

14:41.378 --> 14:43.213
(fireworks pop and squeal)

14:45.916 --> 14:47.584
Say, can you see?

14:47.651 --> 14:48.852
I-I can't see 'em.

14:48.919 --> 14:50.320
They're in the trees.

14:50.387 --> 14:51.654
Steve, snap
out of it.

14:51.722 --> 14:53.756
Mr. Smith, can I speak
to you in the hallway?

14:55.993 --> 14:58.361
Your son appears to
be suffering from ptsd,

14:58.429 --> 14:59.996
Posttraumatic
stress disorder.

15:00.064 --> 15:01.431
But doctor, that's impossible.

15:01.499 --> 15:02.999
He was only in a reenactment.

15:03.067 --> 15:04.133
Oh.

15:04.201 --> 15:06.236
Then it must be ptwrsd,

15:06.303 --> 15:08.505
Posttraumatic
war reenactment stress disorder.

15:08.572 --> 15:09.806
Is that a thing?

15:09.874 --> 15:10.974
I've never
heard of it.

15:11.041 --> 15:12.442
I'd like keep him
here for treatment.

15:12.510 --> 15:14.210
He could be a danger
to himself or others.

15:14.278 --> 15:16.045
Nonsense!

15:16.113 --> 15:17.547
Steve?!

15:17.615 --> 15:19.115
Where'd he go?

15:19.183 --> 15:20.650
When I was out there,

15:20.718 --> 15:22.685
All I wanted to do
was come home.

15:22.753 --> 15:23.987
But now that I'm home,

15:24.054 --> 15:26.022
All I can think about
is getting back there.

15:26.090 --> 15:27.624
The golf course.

15:27.691 --> 15:30.393
Things made more sense
out there.

15:30.461 --> 15:33.029
Here sometimes
someone claims they're a friend,

15:33.097 --> 15:35.031
But they're really
just an acquaintance.

15:35.099 --> 15:37.901
And then, some friends
are really enemies.

15:37.968 --> 15:40.703
I came up
with the word "frenemy."

15:42.673 --> 15:44.073
John,

15:44.141 --> 15:45.608
How did you open the curtain?

15:47.945 --> 15:49.979
Tell me how you
opened the curtain.

15:51.315 --> 15:51.881
John!

15:53.417 --> 15:54.751
(grunts)

15:54.818 --> 15:56.653
<i>...Will be right back.</i>

16:05.143 --> 16:06.477
Hey, there.

16:06.544 --> 16:08.312
The war reenactment
was yesterday.

16:08.380 --> 16:09.113
It's over.

16:09.180 --> 16:10.180
For you, maybe.

16:10.248 --> 16:11.615
Where're you headed?

16:11.683 --> 16:13.984
Just gonna get a grilled
cheese at the snack stop.

16:14.052 --> 16:15.886
I had a friend that
wanted one once.

16:15.954 --> 16:17.521
But he's gone now.

16:17.589 --> 16:19.256
To tucson.

16:19.324 --> 16:20.657
On business.

16:20.725 --> 16:23.427
Won't be back till Wednesday.

16:23.495 --> 16:25.829
I know a place down the road
with a great grilled cheese.

16:25.897 --> 16:26.997
Come on, I'll drive you.

16:27.065 --> 16:27.664
No, thanks.

16:28.833 --> 16:30.467
(golf cart chirps)

16:30.535 --> 16:32.069
I'm not looking for trouble.

16:32.137 --> 16:34.271
Get off the fairway, you turd!

16:34.339 --> 16:36.040
This is the thanks I get.

16:36.107 --> 16:37.674
A hero's welcome.

16:48.019 --> 16:50.554
(gunfire)

16:50.622 --> 16:52.456
(explosion)

16:58.196 --> 16:59.897
We were kids, man.

16:59.964 --> 17:01.598
Buckle couldn't
find his legs.

17:01.666 --> 17:04.300
We were gonna go cruising
when we got home.

17:04.368 --> 17:07.671
We were gonna go cruising
in his solara, man.

17:07.739 --> 17:09.573
Roger:
¶ getting ready
for the best night ¶

17:09.641 --> 17:11.241
¶ the best night
of my life ¶

17:11.309 --> 17:12.876
¶ everything's gonna
be just right ¶

17:12.944 --> 17:15.311
¶ putting on a robe that's warm
but light-- squirt, squirt ¶

17:15.380 --> 17:17.314
¶ best, best, glug, glug,
best, best ¶

17:17.382 --> 17:19.715
¶ get ready,
my tummy is your nest ¶

17:19.784 --> 17:21.617
¶ 'cause I'm stepping
in the best ¶

17:21.685 --> 17:23.420
Ah! Best.

17:24.789 --> 17:27.290
(applause on tv)

17:27.358 --> 17:29.293
Thank you so much.

17:29.360 --> 17:30.694
Shut up.

17:30.762 --> 17:32.096
(applause stops)

17:32.163 --> 17:34.364
You know, celine dion is
in the audience tonight.

17:34.432 --> 17:35.499
(applause)

17:35.567 --> 17:37.634
She's fabulous.

17:37.702 --> 17:39.837
But I'm better. Here we go.

17:39.904 --> 17:44.274
¶ you were my strength
when I was weak ¶

17:44.342 --> 17:47.611
¶ you were my voice
when I couldn't speak ¶

17:47.679 --> 17:48.846
(gong sounds)

17:48.913 --> 17:50.280
¶ you were my... ¶

17:50.348 --> 17:53.117
(sustained note,
distorted into howl)

17:53.184 --> 17:55.252
¶ ¶

18:02.694 --> 18:04.695
¶ ¶

18:06.531 --> 18:09.800
¶ ¶

18:11.769 --> 18:14.204
<i>Streisand:
Thank you. Good night!</i>

18:17.609 --> 18:20.277
So, how'd the big night
turn out?

18:20.345 --> 18:22.112
It was...

18:22.180 --> 18:24.581
There's no word
to describe it.

18:24.649 --> 18:26.483
Schmooblydong?

18:26.551 --> 18:27.985
That's not it,
but it's close.

18:28.052 --> 18:30.854
Let-let me try and put it
in terms you can understand.

18:30.922 --> 18:33.457
Imagine being high
at a rusted root concert

18:33.525 --> 18:36.093
While two dudes take you on
in a sun-baked porta-john.

18:36.161 --> 18:37.594
Wow.

18:37.662 --> 18:39.796
That actually does
sound really good.

18:39.864 --> 18:42.065
Yeah. I'd like that, too.

18:45.970 --> 18:47.504
You're the
boy's father?

18:47.572 --> 18:50.207
Listen, guy, no one can get in
or out of here

18:50.275 --> 18:52.342
Because of that crazy kid,
and we need carts.

18:52.410 --> 18:54.912
That boy is a remorseless
reenactment machine.

18:54.979 --> 18:57.080
I know. I made him.

18:57.148 --> 18:59.683
And I'm the only one
who can get him out.

18:59.751 --> 19:01.451
Stinkfinger, this is
colonel muffdog.

19:01.519 --> 19:02.586
Do you copy? Over.

19:02.654 --> 19:03.854
(static, chirp)

19:03.922 --> 19:05.088
Do you copy?
(static)

19:05.156 --> 19:06.657
Steve:
This is stinkfinger, sir.

19:06.724 --> 19:08.091
They're all dead.

19:08.159 --> 19:09.560
I'm the last one.

19:09.627 --> 19:11.328
Your mission is complete.

19:11.396 --> 19:12.729
Return to base.

19:12.797 --> 19:14.064
I can't do that, sir.

19:14.132 --> 19:15.632
I'm not good enough yet.

19:15.700 --> 19:16.934
Good enough at what, soldier?

19:17.001 --> 19:17.901
I can do better.

19:17.969 --> 19:19.803
That's why I came here.

19:19.871 --> 19:22.639
It's the only place
you were ever proud of me, sir.

19:22.707 --> 19:25.442
It wasn't the war.

19:25.510 --> 19:27.244
I'm going in.

19:32.917 --> 19:34.084
Stay back!

19:34.152 --> 19:35.519
Easy, stinkfinger. Easy.

19:35.587 --> 19:37.854
It wasn't the war
that made you this way.

19:37.922 --> 19:39.122
Wh-what do you mean?

19:39.190 --> 19:40.791
Oh, steve, it was me!

19:40.858 --> 19:43.694
I pushed you too hard,
put too much pressure on you.

19:43.761 --> 19:45.862
But I only did it
because I love you

19:45.930 --> 19:47.497
And want you to succeed!

19:47.565 --> 19:49.533
But you don't need
to be pushed,

19:49.601 --> 19:51.368
'cause you're doing great
on your own.

19:51.436 --> 19:53.270
(crying)

19:56.207 --> 19:59.943
I did to you
what america did to vietnam.

20:00.011 --> 20:01.778
I tried to control you.

20:01.846 --> 20:03.413
But no longer.

20:03.481 --> 20:05.515
I'm pulling out of you, steve.

20:05.583 --> 20:07.184
I'm pulling out.

20:07.252 --> 20:09.453
I'm sorry if I hurt you, son.

20:18.696 --> 20:20.864
(fireworks pop)

20:22.300 --> 20:24.268
The celebration's
still going on.

20:24.335 --> 20:26.136
You know, you
could still sing.

20:26.204 --> 20:27.704
Am I good enough now?

20:27.772 --> 20:29.473
You were always
good enough, steve.

20:29.540 --> 20:32.142
I don't know where this low
self-esteem is coming from,

20:32.210 --> 20:34.177
But you need to start
believing in yourself.

20:34.245 --> 20:36.213
So go out there and sing.

20:36.281 --> 20:39.349
And any way you do it,
I'm gonna love it.

20:47.158 --> 20:50.727
¶ oh, say ¶

20:50.795 --> 20:54.164
¶ can you see,
by the dawn's early light? ¶

20:54.232 --> 20:57.534
¶ girl, I'm gonna rock you
in freedom town tonight ¶

20:57.602 --> 21:00.671
That's my...
Neighbor son.

21:00.738 --> 21:02.139
¶ you know
you never felt so good ¶

21:02.206 --> 21:03.874
¶ no, you never
felt so right ¶

